Kowloon's Jade Magistracy has been compiling geological survey data from the Cinderteeth Mountains for two years, and the Glasswash Fans represent one of the most minerally significant zones on the continent. Before survey teams can safely enter the obsidian harvest areas, the hostile element population requires field assessment: fan crawlers are pushing through survey approach corridors, mirror-blind hunters are targeting survey instruments as reflective prey, and crystal resonance sprites are interfering with measurement equipment. Engage one of each and return the field report data.
The Glasswash hostile element assessment is complete and Kowloon's survey teams have entered the obsidian harvest areas under escort. The Jade Magistracy notes that the crystal resonance sprites were actively interfering with survey instruments in a pattern suggesting the Yellow Garden is not simply wild territory but a zone that reacts to measurement activity — a finding that has elevated the Magistracy's interest in what the Glasswash Fans might be concealing.
